body:
Sorting cells topologically to speed things up in some cases.

TODOs:
- [x] Add code for sorting cells topologically
- [x] Create a small example design that demonstrates the issue
- [x] Add runtime option (scratchpad flag) for restoring old behavior
- [ ] Double-check that there are no passes for which topological sort order is the worst case
- [ ] Add a `module->rcells()` method for iterating over the cells in reverse sort order

Short demo:

```
claire@lamarr:~/Work/yosys$ cat demo.sv 
module test (input [7:0] A, B, output [7:0] X);
  wire [7:0] B1, B2, C1, C2, D1, D2, E1, E2;
  assign X = B1 + B2;
  assign B1 = C1 + D2, B2 = C2 + D1;
  assign C1 = D1 + A, C2 = A + D2;
  assign D1 = E1 + B, D2 = E2 + B;
  assign E1 = A + B, E2 = B + A;
endmodule

